        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "at least with this change in codelens.lua line 255 does not look ugly as hell. This places the reference at the level of the first char.\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/ff68fd6b8a84ce83c14358db1d70a562f1524ebe/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua#L255\n\nlocal line = api.nvim_buf_get_lines(bufnr, row, row + 1, false)[1] or \"\"\nlocal first_char_col = #line:match(\"^%s*\") \nlocal virt_text = { { string.rep(' ', first_char_col), 'LspCodeLensSeparator' }, }\n\n<img width=\"375\" height=\"345\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7f9f9c6f-bba4-4649-a318-b42d592fadac\" />",
            "created_at": "2026-04-21T21:50:31Z",
