        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Sorry to bring this up, but we need a more subtle and minimal default presentation. The current behavior is distracting.\n\nWhile relying on the LSP server is a reasonable approach, we should still provide a solid, sane default on our side. I believe most IDEs define their own positioning for CodeLens rather than relying entirely on the ranges returned by the server (maybe LSP spec need to work on this).\n\nThe only way I’ve found to fix this is to override the entire `vim.lsp.codelens` with a custom implementation.\n\n```lua\nvim.lsp.codelens = require \"user.lsp.codelens\"\n```\n\nHowever, this approach isn’t ideal, as it would make it harder to receive future updates.\n\n### 💀\n<img width=\"453\" height=\"227\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f9f561e1-e151-4c4e-b5fb-8e95e584d163\" />",
            "created_at": "2026-04-23T06:51:48Z",
